text.section:
Every lot of severed turf grass sod, plugs, and sprigs, as defined under this subtitle, which is sold, exposed for sale, installed, transported, or advertised within the State for planting purposes by a dealer shall be accompanied by or have attached to the bill of lading, bill of sale, sales slip, or invoice a label containing the following information plainly written or printed in the English language:
The recognized common names;
The variety of each component;
The texture, origin, and net measure;
The presence of restricted noxious weeds;
The name and address of the dealer who labeled the lot; and
If the kind or mixture is not known, this fact shall be stated.
